        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 9:05PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 905 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms 9 miles northeast of Forsyth, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Miles City, Rosebud, Moon Creek Ranch, Hathaway, Matthews
Recreation Area, Twelve Mile Dam, Garland, Strawberry Hill
Recreation Area, Angela, Cartersville and Rock Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

Locally heavy rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may
lead to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
